block content
  .tbgl
    .container
      .row.center-text
        .span12
          h1 <i class="icon-github-sign"></i> Gitignore.io
          h6 Generate .gitignore files
      .row.well.space
        .span12
          .controls
            .span8
              input.input-block-level#ignoreSearch(type='hidden')
            button.btn.btn-inverse.span3(type='submit', onClick='generateGitIgnore()') Generate File
  .tbgb
    .container
      .row
        .span12
          h3 Command Line
          p You can run Gitignore.io from your command line as long as you have an active internet connection.  You need to add a function to your environment that lets you access the Gitignore.io API.
          blockquote
            h5 OSX
            pre $ sudo echo "function gi() { curl http://gitignore.io/api/\$@ ;}"  >> ~/.profile && source ~/.profile
            h5 Linux
            pre $ sudo echo "function gi() { curl http://gitignore.io/api/\$@ ;}"  >> ~/.bash_profile && source ~/.bash_profile
          p After the function is created, you can type <code># gi linux,java</code> and you'll get a Linux and Java gitignore file.
          blockquote
            h5 Usage for display
            pre $ gi linux,java
              | # Generated by http://gitignore.io
              | &nbsp;
              | ### Linux ###
              | .*
              | !.gitignore
              | *~
              | &nbsp;
              | ### Java ###
              | *.class
              | &nbsp;
              | # Package Files #
              | *.jar
              | *.war
              | *.ear
            h5 Usage for adding to file
            pre $ gi linux,java >> .gitignore
